est protocells. Morowitz views origin of life issues from the perspective of certain constructs in the philosophy of science that provide guideposts to formulating and assessing hypotheses. This book presents a unique discussion among origin-of-life books on the relation between science and epistemology on the difficult problem of learning about the very distant past.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aLifexOrigin. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aArrowsmith, William, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000z97831105380140 cprintz978030005483540uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030019427240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300194272423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300194272/original  a978-3-11-053801-4  Yale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY